WEBVTT

00:01.131 --> 00:03.699
Hey, doggie!

00:03.829 --> 00:05.875
♪♪

00:06.006 --> 00:07.529
Beautiful garden.

00:07.659 --> 00:08.573
Hmm.

00:08.704 --> 00:09.922
♪♪

00:10.053 --> 00:11.054
[doorbell rings]

00:11.185 --> 00:12.708
Greetings.
My name is Evan Huang,

00:12.838 --> 00:15.450
and I'm a volunteer
for the United States Census.

00:15.580 --> 00:17.800
Do you have a moment
to answer a few questions?

00:17.930 --> 00:20.020
[gasps]

00:20.150 --> 00:22.370
[suspenseful music plays]

00:22.500 --> 00:27.331
♪♪

00:29.159 --> 00:31.205
-A bowl of chili...
-[chuckles]

00:31.335 --> 00:33.120
...an Ernest Goes To...
movie on the TV...

00:33.250 --> 00:34.599
Ow!

00:34.730 --> 00:36.166
...doesn't get
much better than this.

00:36.297 --> 00:38.125
[door opens][both laugh]

00:38.255 --> 00:39.126
Dad, Dad!

00:39.256 --> 00:40.388
Evan, are you okay?

00:40.518 --> 00:42.346
I don't know.
I saw something.

00:42.477 --> 00:44.131
What happened?
What'd you see?

00:44.261 --> 00:45.393
I saw...

00:45.523 --> 00:47.134
[softly]
other Chinese people.

00:47.264 --> 00:48.352
[gasps]

00:48.483 --> 00:50.615
♪♪

00:50.746 --> 00:51.790
♪ Fresh off the boat♪

00:51.921 --> 00:53.531
♪ I'm gettin' mine
everywhere I go♪

00:53.662 --> 00:55.533
♪ If you don't know, homey,
now you know♪

00:55.664 --> 00:57.579
♪ Fresh off the boat♪

00:57.709 --> 00:59.581
♪ Homey, you don't know
where I come from♪

00:59.711 --> 01:00.799
♪ But I know where I'm goin'♪

01:00.930 --> 01:03.846
♪ I'm fresh off the boat♪

01:03.976 --> 01:05.848
So you saw
a Chinese couple?

01:05.978 --> 01:08.198
Yep. They must've just moved
to the neighborhood.

01:08.329 --> 01:09.591
[laughs]
I dreamed this day would come.

01:09.721 --> 01:10.635
I have to tell your mother.

01:10.766 --> 01:11.723
Uh, sorry, pal,

01:11.854 --> 01:13.160
but we're gonna have to
put a pin in our plans.

01:13.290 --> 01:14.204
Oh, just a reminder now.

01:14.335 --> 01:16.076
Honey and I
only have small windows

01:16.206 --> 01:17.642
between baby naps
to have fun.

01:17.773 --> 01:19.209
I taped
the last season of ER,

01:19.340 --> 01:22.299
and I am going to devour it
one nap at a time.

01:22.430 --> 01:23.996
Uh-huh.
You know,
for a while there,

01:24.127 --> 01:25.998
I thought the show
was called Er.

01:26.129 --> 01:28.827
I keep begging her,
give Chicago Hopea shot,

01:28.958 --> 01:30.090
but she won't have it.

01:31.743 --> 01:32.788
He's long gone.

01:32.918 --> 01:33.876
♪♪

01:34.006 --> 01:36.008
DEIDRE: Okay, ladies.

01:36.139 --> 01:37.227
First point of business

01:37.358 --> 01:38.620
is the annual fundraiser.

01:38.750 --> 01:39.664
This year, we're gonna be

01:39.795 --> 01:41.275
taking donations to refurbish

01:41.405 --> 01:42.450
the "We Are The World" mural

01:42.580 --> 01:43.668
at the Community Center.

01:43.799 --> 01:46.584
♪♪

01:46.715 --> 01:48.369
Why are all the kids
white?

01:48.499 --> 01:50.240
I've got a better idea.

01:50.371 --> 01:52.286
Tear down this racist mural

01:52.416 --> 01:54.418
so we can move on
to addressing the epidemic

01:54.549 --> 01:56.594
that is destroying
our neighborhood.

01:56.725 --> 01:58.379
And what, pray tell,
might that be?

01:58.509 --> 02:00.120
Three words.

02:00.250 --> 02:01.556
Low rise jeans.

02:01.686 --> 02:03.471
-Oh, come on!
-They're very flattering.

02:03.601 --> 02:05.560
This trendy jean
is a menace.

02:05.690 --> 02:09.085
Every time I step outside,
all I see are Whale Tails.

02:09.216 --> 02:10.130
Whale Tails?

02:10.260 --> 02:11.131
T-shaped underwear

02:11.261 --> 02:13.220
sticking out
the top of jeans.

02:13.350 --> 02:14.482
It's disgusting.

02:14.612 --> 02:15.570
Jessica, the HOA

02:15.700 --> 02:17.224
cannot enforce a dress code.

02:17.354 --> 02:19.095
And frankly,

02:19.226 --> 02:21.141
if beautiful celebrities
like Rene Russo can wear them,

02:21.271 --> 02:23.926
then so can the beautiful mamas
in this subdivision.

02:24.056 --> 02:25.232
Am I right?

02:25.362 --> 02:26.842
[laughter]

02:26.972 --> 02:28.887
I'm surrounded
by tramps.

02:29.018 --> 02:32.195
[indistinct conversations]

02:32.326 --> 02:34.284
What is it, Louis?
I'm extremely angry,

02:34.415 --> 02:35.720
so whatever it is
you have to say,

02:35.851 --> 02:37.331
I will likely respond
poorly to.

02:37.461 --> 02:39.507
There's another Chinese family
in the neighborhood!

02:39.637 --> 02:40.856
[gasps]

02:42.466 --> 02:44.381
I cannot go
to that community pool again.

02:44.512 --> 02:45.643
The water is filthy.

02:45.774 --> 02:47.515
EVAN: [scoffs]

02:47.645 --> 02:50.257
Whoa, buddy,
it's okay.

02:50.387 --> 02:51.258
We all reach a point in our

02:51.388 --> 02:52.737
lives when our interest in girls

02:52.868 --> 02:54.086
reaches a whole new level.

02:54.217 --> 02:56.611
Gross. No.

02:56.741 --> 02:59.222
I'm hiding the private data
I've gathered for the Census.

02:59.353 --> 03:00.441
You always find

03:00.571 --> 03:02.138
fresh ways to be boring.

03:02.269 --> 03:04.227
Um, why is there
a photo of a classy woman

03:04.358 --> 03:05.272
above your desk?

03:05.402 --> 03:07.187
That's
Martha Farnsworth Riche.

03:07.317 --> 03:08.536
The Director of the Census,

03:08.666 --> 03:10.146
a.k.a. my boss, a.k.a.

03:10.277 --> 03:11.452
what gets me up in the morning.

03:11.582 --> 03:13.628
So boring,
it's amazing.

03:13.758 --> 03:15.369
I'm entrusted to ask citizens

03:15.499 --> 03:17.153
questions about their household,

03:17.284 --> 03:18.676
and they trust me
as a Census-taker

03:18.807 --> 03:20.678
to answer those questions
honestly.

03:20.809 --> 03:22.289
Nothing boring
about that.

03:22.419 --> 03:24.552
♪♪

03:24.682 --> 03:26.380
If we worked
for the Census,

03:26.510 --> 03:27.642
we could ask people
whatever we wanted,

03:27.772 --> 03:29.296
and they would
haveto answer.

03:29.426 --> 03:30.993
But we don't work
for the Census.

03:31.123 --> 03:32.690
Or do we?

03:32.821 --> 03:34.170
♪♪

03:34.301 --> 03:36.520
So this is the house
where Evan saw them?

03:36.651 --> 03:38.261
Split-level, not bad.

03:38.392 --> 03:40.959
Come on, let's go
knock on the door and
introduce ourselves.

03:41.090 --> 03:42.178
Oh, wait.

03:43.571 --> 03:44.572
Is it too much?

03:44.702 --> 03:46.356
That tree is beautiful.

03:46.487 --> 03:48.315
I just don't want
our first impression

03:48.445 --> 03:50.099
to be trespassing
on their property

03:50.230 --> 03:52.101
while holding
a really specific present.

03:52.232 --> 03:54.364
You're right. What we need is
an idyllic meet-cute moment,

03:54.495 --> 03:56.323
like in the best
romantic comedies.
Mm-hmm.

03:56.453 --> 03:58.803
We each drop an orange
at the grocery store.

03:58.934 --> 04:01.545
We bend down to pick it up,
and then we all lock eyes.

04:01.676 --> 04:04.374
Some song from The Cure plays,
and we're off to the races.

04:04.505 --> 04:05.332
That's good.

04:05.462 --> 04:07.464
Or we follow them
when they leave the house

04:07.595 --> 04:08.378
and bump into them
in public.

04:08.509 --> 04:09.466
Oh, I love it.

04:11.163 --> 04:14.254
They're really taking their time
at this all-you-can-eat buffet.

04:14.384 --> 04:15.342
Well,
it's a great sign.

04:15.472 --> 04:17.344
Our mutual love of
quantity-over-quality food

04:17.474 --> 04:19.041
will be the bedrock
of our friendship.

04:19.171 --> 04:20.260
[door opens]

04:20.390 --> 04:22.479
There they are.

04:22.610 --> 04:24.351
They're beautiful.

04:24.481 --> 04:26.004
But where are
their to-go boxes?

04:26.135 --> 04:28.616
Would we ever leave
an all-you-can-eat restaurant

04:28.746 --> 04:30.095
without ribs
for the road?

04:30.226 --> 04:31.488
[car door opens]They're at their car.
It's time.

04:31.619 --> 04:33.185
Okay. Remember.

04:33.316 --> 04:34.274
When we meet them,

04:34.404 --> 04:36.319
let's just play it cool
and see how it goes.

04:36.450 --> 04:37.320
No promises.

04:38.669 --> 04:39.714
Let me just get our prop,
and we'll head over.

04:39.844 --> 04:42.238
We'll stroll by, pretending
to read this newspaper,

04:42.369 --> 04:43.457
and look surprised
to see them.

04:43.587 --> 04:44.284
Sound good?

04:44.414 --> 04:46.198
Oh -- Jessica?

04:46.329 --> 04:47.765
[squeals]

04:49.245 --> 04:51.813
We're so happy
you're here.

04:51.943 --> 04:53.858
[laughs]

04:53.989 --> 04:55.599
We've dreamed
of this day.

04:55.730 --> 04:58.298
♪♪

04:58.428 --> 04:59.864
Us, too.

04:59.995 --> 05:01.431
Us, too.

05:02.476 --> 05:03.607
[gasps]

05:03.738 --> 05:06.393
Is that a take-out box
in your purse?

05:06.523 --> 05:07.611
ELAINE: It is.

05:07.742 --> 05:09.613
[laughter]

05:09.744 --> 05:11.267
[voice breaking]
We're so happy you're here.

05:14.618 --> 05:16.272
Taiwan, two years ago.

05:16.403 --> 05:18.056
That's the last time
we saw Chinese people

05:18.187 --> 05:19.188
that weren't family.

05:19.319 --> 05:21.451
Mm.
Three years ago for us.

05:21.582 --> 05:23.366
Back where we lived
in Georgia,

05:23.497 --> 05:25.412
we once saw
a Chinese face

05:25.542 --> 05:27.327
in the window
of a passing bus.

05:27.457 --> 05:28.545
Wow, near miss.

05:28.676 --> 05:30.068
No, no,
we chased after the bus.

05:30.199 --> 05:32.288
Ran six blocks,
full speed.

05:32.419 --> 05:34.072
Caught up to the bus
at the next stop,

05:34.203 --> 05:36.336
but I didn't have any change
to get on board.

05:36.466 --> 05:38.468
So I yelled, "Chinese face.
I've been looking for you.

05:38.599 --> 05:40.383
Get off the bus."
[sighs]

05:40.514 --> 05:42.690
He thought about it
and said no.

05:42.820 --> 05:44.300
He'd already paid
for the fare.

05:44.431 --> 05:45.606
Ohh, so Chinese.

05:45.736 --> 05:48.217
Disappointing, but I get
where he's coming from.

05:48.348 --> 05:50.045
Mm-hmm.Long story short,

05:50.175 --> 05:51.481
we're very happy
to have met you.

05:51.612 --> 05:52.439
[laughter]

05:52.569 --> 05:54.658
So, how are you
liking Orlando?

05:54.789 --> 05:55.790
Oh, I love it,

05:55.920 --> 05:58.445
but the humidity
is killing my hair.

05:58.575 --> 06:00.621
I'm usually four times
more beautiful than this.

06:00.751 --> 06:01.578
Me, too.

06:01.709 --> 06:03.014
But the reduction
in beauty

06:03.145 --> 06:05.234
means less Jewish guys
hit on me at the gas pump.

06:05.365 --> 06:06.278
Oh.

06:06.409 --> 06:08.063
Okay, serious question.

06:09.281 --> 06:11.588
Are there any grocers here
that sell tofu?

06:11.719 --> 06:13.590
There were none
in Georgia.

06:13.721 --> 06:14.635
I miss tofu so much.

06:14.765 --> 06:16.506
Took months to find.

06:16.637 --> 06:18.116
Greeno's in Rose Isle.

06:18.247 --> 06:20.292
The hippie owner Pam
wears a bandana on her head.

06:20.423 --> 06:21.729
Oh, you're a lifesaver.

06:21.859 --> 06:23.861
I'll have my son, Horace,
pick some up for me.

06:23.992 --> 06:25.385
Oh, you have a son, too!

06:25.515 --> 06:27.604
I have three --
Eddie, Emery, and Evan.

06:27.735 --> 06:29.563
Three sons?

06:29.693 --> 06:31.260
Oh, you must be so proud.

06:31.391 --> 06:33.741
Well, the first two are...

06:33.871 --> 06:34.959
solid.

06:35.090 --> 06:37.397
But my youngest, Evan,
he's a real genius.

06:37.527 --> 06:38.441
He recently
skipped a grade.

06:38.572 --> 06:40.487
Sounds just like
my Horace.

06:40.617 --> 06:43.533
He skipped 2 grades,
went to Harvard at 16,

06:43.664 --> 06:45.100
and now runs
his own small business.

06:45.230 --> 06:46.841
You're living the dream.

06:46.971 --> 06:48.103
Mm.

06:48.233 --> 06:51.280
I love that you opened
an American steakhouse.

06:51.411 --> 06:53.151
Well, you know,
I'm Chinese through and through,

06:53.282 --> 06:54.718
but I'm 100% American.

06:54.849 --> 06:55.676
Oh, me, too.

06:55.806 --> 06:57.112
I mean,
if I had a choice,

06:57.242 --> 06:58.548
I'd eat apple pie
for breakfast.

06:58.679 --> 07:00.376
My favorite cut of steak
is "any."

07:00.507 --> 07:01.595
When asked
if I'm religious,

07:01.725 --> 07:03.118
I say I believe
in the Dallas Cowboys.

07:03.248 --> 07:05.425
My firstborn's middle name
is "Elvis."

07:05.555 --> 07:06.730
When I'm on hold
on the phone,

07:06.861 --> 07:08.558
I doodle bald eagles
on a notepad.

07:08.689 --> 07:09.690
When the wife and kids
are out of town,

07:09.820 --> 07:11.169
I roll my own cigarettes,

07:11.300 --> 07:13.433
and I light them with a match
I strike off my boot.

07:13.563 --> 07:14.999
[laughs]

07:15.130 --> 07:16.436
[laughs]

07:16.566 --> 07:19.177
[sighs] So, at
the grocery store last week,

07:19.308 --> 07:21.353
a stranger came up to me
and asked

07:21.484 --> 07:23.399
which aisle
the soy sauce was in.

07:23.530 --> 07:26.184
Did you tell him
it was in "Aisle Slap"?

07:26.315 --> 07:27.229
No.

07:27.359 --> 07:28.796
I did know where it was,
so I told him.

07:28.926 --> 07:31.451
But afterwards
in the car,

07:31.581 --> 07:33.148
I screamed
for like 10 minutes.

07:33.278 --> 07:36.586
My HOA wanted to refurbish
a "We Are The World" mural

07:36.717 --> 07:38.327
that only has white children
in it.

07:38.458 --> 07:39.763
Ugh.
I voted to tear it down,

07:39.894 --> 07:41.461
but they don't see
the problem.

07:41.591 --> 07:43.637
Forget tearing it down.

07:43.767 --> 07:45.726
Make them add
an Asian face to it.

07:45.856 --> 07:46.770
[sighs]

07:46.901 --> 07:48.816
Trust me, my HOA
has more white ladies

07:48.946 --> 07:50.426
than a Neil Diamond
concert,

07:50.557 --> 07:52.428
except they're not aroused --
They're bitter,

07:52.559 --> 07:53.690
and they won't listen.

07:53.821 --> 07:54.996
Oh, they will this time.

07:55.126 --> 07:57.041
Now that
there's two of us here,

07:57.172 --> 07:59.566
we can set them up
for a Racism Trap.

07:59.696 --> 08:02.525
I hate racism,
and I love a trap.

08:02.656 --> 08:03.700
Tell me more.

08:05.789 --> 08:08.836
Hi, I'm Rick, and this is
my assistant, Claude.

08:08.966 --> 08:10.272
We work for the Census.

08:10.402 --> 08:12.143
Do you mind if we ask you
a few questions?

08:12.274 --> 08:13.580
Sure, be happy to.

08:13.710 --> 08:14.624
Great.

08:14.755 --> 08:15.538
How many people live
in your household?

08:15.669 --> 08:17.366
Just two,
me and my husband.

08:17.497 --> 08:18.976
Great.
And do you have a pool?

08:19.107 --> 08:20.195
Yes, we do.

08:20.325 --> 08:21.239
[chuckles]

08:21.370 --> 08:23.590
Oh, excellent,
excellent.

08:23.720 --> 08:26.462
And what hours do you leave
this pool unattended?

08:26.593 --> 08:27.768
A, all day?

08:27.898 --> 08:29.465
B, 9:00 to 5:00?

08:29.596 --> 08:30.858
C, Nights and weekends?

08:30.988 --> 08:33.034
Or D, Other,
please specify.

08:33.164 --> 08:34.383
♪♪

08:34.514 --> 08:37.647
[indistinct conversations]

08:37.778 --> 08:40.650
Jessica, relax on the pastries.
Let's get this meeting started.

08:40.781 --> 08:43.653
Um, I'm not Jessica.

08:43.784 --> 08:46.090
Oh, do we all
look alike to you?

08:46.221 --> 08:47.744
Um...

08:47.875 --> 08:49.050
No?
[chuckles nervously]

08:49.180 --> 08:50.965
She was turned around, she has
black hair, and she's wearing

08:51.095 --> 08:52.401
that same dress
that you always wear.

08:52.532 --> 08:54.708
Though I must say,
she wears it better.

08:54.838 --> 08:57.493
Do you ever mix up any
of these other ladies' names?

08:57.624 --> 09:00.888
I wonder what's different
about me and Elaine.

09:01.018 --> 09:02.716
Hmm...
Hmm...

09:02.846 --> 09:04.500
[women murmuring]

09:04.631 --> 09:06.328
Okay. What can I do
to fix this?

09:06.458 --> 09:07.764
That mural
you're repainting?

09:07.895 --> 09:09.549
Make one of those white kids
Chinese.

09:09.679 --> 09:11.855
And the kid's eyes
need to be the same size

09:11.986 --> 09:12.900
as all the others.

09:13.030 --> 09:14.815
None of that
lines-for-eyes crap.

09:14.945 --> 09:16.033
Deal.

09:16.164 --> 09:18.296
Okay. So we good?
All forgiven?

09:18.427 --> 09:19.776
Jessica, are we good,

09:19.907 --> 09:21.691
or is there anything else
that would help you

09:21.822 --> 09:23.563
to feel better
about this situation?

09:23.693 --> 09:24.694
♪♪

09:24.825 --> 09:26.566
...so then Elaine
gave me the opening,

09:26.696 --> 09:29.133
and I made Deidre
ban low rise jeans.

09:29.264 --> 09:31.571
Oh, great, because I know that's
coming to men's fashion soon,

09:31.701 --> 09:33.094
and I am not comfortable
with it.

09:33.224 --> 09:35.226
[sighs] I've never met
someone like her,

09:35.357 --> 09:37.228
you know,
someone who is almost my equal.

09:37.359 --> 09:39.927
We're so in sync,
like that music group,

09:40.057 --> 09:41.232
Backstreet Boys.

09:41.363 --> 09:43.583
Julius is just as amazing.
He's so cool.

09:43.713 --> 09:45.019
And you know
I'm pretty cool, too,

09:45.149 --> 09:46.586
so we're totally vibing
off of each other.

09:46.716 --> 09:47.587
It's cool.

09:47.717 --> 09:48.588
Guess we're talking
about you now.

09:48.718 --> 09:50.764
He's coming over tomorrow
to watch the Cowboys game.

09:50.894 --> 09:52.026
And Marvin's
gonna come by, as well.

09:52.156 --> 09:53.070
Three bulls.

09:53.201 --> 09:54.115
Okay, back to me,

09:55.464 --> 09:56.291
Elaine is taking me to brunch
in the morning.

09:56.421 --> 09:58.685
But you hate brunch. You call it
lazy man's breakfast.

09:58.815 --> 10:00.861
If Elaine likes it,
I'll give it a shot.

10:00.991 --> 10:03.037
Apparently,
you can drink during the day,

10:03.167 --> 10:04.821
and it's not sad.

10:04.952 --> 10:06.562
[knock on door]

10:06.693 --> 10:09.565
Hi! My name is Evan Huang,
and I'm with the U.S. Census.

10:09.696 --> 10:11.828
Another Census
questionnaire?

10:11.959 --> 10:14.526
I just answered one yesterday
with two other Asian kids.

10:14.657 --> 10:17.138
Sorry, I can't handle
any more questions

10:17.268 --> 10:18.182
about my pool.

10:18.313 --> 10:19.967
Pool?

10:21.185 --> 10:22.839
Lord, give me strength,

10:22.970 --> 10:25.755
for I am a quivering volcano
of rage.

10:25.886 --> 10:28.715
A toast to our success
at the HOA.

10:28.845 --> 10:29.716
The mural is down.

10:29.846 --> 10:31.152
And the jeans are up.
Mm.

10:31.282 --> 10:32.632
[glasses clink]

10:32.762 --> 10:34.677
If we have nothing else,
we have each other's back.

10:34.808 --> 10:36.592
We need to find
our next target.

10:36.723 --> 10:38.072
Mm.
There's a man
down my street

10:38.202 --> 10:39.726
with a Shih Tzu
named "Chinatown"

10:39.856 --> 10:41.162
that needs to be
taken down a notch.

10:41.292 --> 10:42.642
Oh, I forgot to tell you.

10:42.772 --> 10:44.818
My son drove to that tofu place
you recommended

10:44.948 --> 10:45.862
and picked some up.

10:45.993 --> 10:46.776
What a sweet young man.

10:46.907 --> 10:48.212
You know,
I sent Eddie once,

10:48.343 --> 10:49.997
and he came back
with pizza and a lamp.

10:50.127 --> 10:52.739
Oh. [chuckles]
Mm.

10:52.869 --> 10:55.524
♪♪

10:55.655 --> 10:56.917
I've never
done this before,

10:57.047 --> 10:59.571
but this moment
feels so right.

11:00.529 --> 11:02.444
Elaine Lee,

11:02.574 --> 11:05.099
will you do me the honor
of giving me parenting advice?

11:05.229 --> 11:07.623
Jessica.

11:07.754 --> 11:09.886
Of course. I'd love to.

11:10.017 --> 11:11.453
Horace is
such a great kid.

11:11.583 --> 11:13.803
I want my sons
to turn out just like him.

11:13.934 --> 11:15.805
Well, for me,

11:15.936 --> 11:18.460
the key was
confusing the child.

11:18.590 --> 11:21.637
If he got an A,
sometimes I'd act happy,

11:21.768 --> 11:23.378
and sometimes
I'd be displeased.

11:23.508 --> 11:26.207
He never knew what was coming,
so he worked even harder.

11:26.337 --> 11:29.471
So instead of no praise,
inconsistent praise.

11:29.601 --> 11:31.473
Mm-hmm.Oh, I love it.

11:31.603 --> 11:33.562
Try it and report back.

11:33.693 --> 11:35.869
[sighs] Well, uh,
shall we get the check?
Sure.

11:35.999 --> 11:37.784
I've had
a couple of drinks.

11:37.914 --> 11:40.351
I'm gonna go call Horace
to get me a ride home.

11:40.482 --> 11:42.397
Excuse me.

11:42.527 --> 11:46.183
[jazz piano plays]

11:46.314 --> 11:48.838
I'm friends
with Chinese Oprah.

11:48.969 --> 11:49.752
[chuckles]

11:49.883 --> 11:52.494
I'm Chinese Gayle.

11:52.624 --> 11:53.887
♪♪

11:54.017 --> 11:55.845
So, you're
a big football fan, huh?

11:55.976 --> 11:57.020
I am,
but the last couple years,

11:57.151 --> 11:59.370
I've been so busy
with the restaurant,
I've fallen off a bit.

11:59.501 --> 12:00.850
Mm-hmm.

12:00.981 --> 12:02.765
Hey, hey, hey.
Sorry I'm late.

12:02.896 --> 12:04.811
I finally got Maria
down for her nap,

12:04.941 --> 12:06.421
though she'll probably
get up any second now.

12:06.551 --> 12:08.728
No, let the patient die,
Margulies.

12:08.858 --> 12:10.468
It's your relationship
with Clooney

12:10.599 --> 12:11.818
that's on life support.

12:11.948 --> 12:13.689
Uh, Marvin, Julius.
Julius, Marvin.

12:13.820 --> 12:14.734
Hey.Great to meet you.

12:14.864 --> 12:16.518
Julius, all right.
[laughs]Yeah.

12:16.648 --> 12:17.954
Whoa.
Yeah.

12:18.085 --> 12:19.260
Are those
homemade tortilla chips?

12:19.390 --> 12:20.696
Oh, yeah.Oh!

12:20.827 --> 12:22.176
I spent the summer
after junior high

12:22.306 --> 12:23.481
hitchhiking
through Mexico.

12:23.612 --> 12:26.093
I met a little, uh,
chica bonita

12:26.223 --> 12:28.399
who taught me how to make love
and cook with lard.

12:28.530 --> 12:29.531
Yeah.
[laughs]

12:29.661 --> 12:31.272
Hey, so are your guys
putting up a fight,

12:31.402 --> 12:32.316
or did Michael Irvin

12:32.447 --> 12:33.883
have them at the strip club
all night?

12:34.014 --> 12:35.406
Oh, hey.
Wouldn't matter.

12:35.537 --> 12:36.843
Your Dolphins start
a 50-year-old QB

12:36.973 --> 12:38.888
with a knee brace
the size of an oil barrel.

12:39.019 --> 12:39.889
Hoo-hoo!
[laughs]

12:40.020 --> 12:42.065
Uh-oh, a couple ball busters
going at it.

12:42.196 --> 12:44.285
Yeah, you on the ledge
about passing on Randy Moss

12:44.415 --> 12:46.504
for that 8th pick, huh?Ah. No, don't need him.

12:46.635 --> 12:48.724
Chan Gailey's offense
has looked really good.

12:48.855 --> 12:49.986
Yeah.
Wait,
who's Chan Gailey?

12:51.683 --> 12:51.727
Gailey's helped you guys out.
I have to admit that.Uh-huh.

12:53.207 --> 12:54.121
I liked his concepts
for Kordell Stewart
at Pittsburgh.

12:54.251 --> 12:55.862
Thank God he didn't
try to put Aikman in
the "slash" role here.

12:55.992 --> 12:57.994
Aikman at flanker?[both laugh]

12:58.125 --> 13:01.258
[laughs]
Aikman? No way.

13:01.389 --> 13:02.303
Okay, whoa.

13:02.433 --> 13:04.479
These chips you made
are insane.

13:04.609 --> 13:06.046
Mm-hmm.Do you make a lot
of stuff at home?

13:06.176 --> 13:07.482
As much as I can.

13:07.612 --> 13:08.918
Right now, my passion
is homemade sausage.

13:09.049 --> 13:10.746
Oh, I love making
homemade sausage.

13:10.877 --> 13:12.008
I find the key is,

13:12.139 --> 13:13.923
the quality
of the intestines...The quality
of the intestines...

13:14.054 --> 13:15.359
...for the casings....for the casings.

13:15.490 --> 13:16.883
What?!
[laughs]

13:17.013 --> 13:17.971
Oh, all right.

13:18.101 --> 13:19.276
You're all right.
Yeah.

13:19.407 --> 13:21.365
Uh, you know,
I've never been a-a sausage guy.

13:21.496 --> 13:22.976
I'm more of a bacon man
myself.

13:23.106 --> 13:24.281
So what's
your go-to meat grinder?

13:24.412 --> 13:25.979
It's not
about the machine.

13:26.109 --> 13:27.937
It's about the man
behind the machine.

13:28.068 --> 13:28.808
Oh, yeah.
Yeah.

13:28.938 --> 13:30.722
Hmm. Yeah.[laughs]

13:30.853 --> 13:32.550
Oh, I would love that.Yeah. Oh, that's me.

13:32.681 --> 13:33.682
Hey,
can I give you a ride?

13:33.813 --> 13:34.683
Oh, sure.

13:34.814 --> 13:36.380
It's so nice
Horace called you a cab.

13:36.511 --> 13:37.555
Called?

13:37.686 --> 13:40.036
No, he's driving the cab.[horn honks]

13:40.167 --> 13:40.820
Hey, Mom.

13:42.299 --> 13:43.387
Somebody was just wearing
Jordache cologne in here.

13:43.518 --> 13:44.954
Just want to let you know.

13:49.916 --> 13:51.352
How have the fares
been today?

13:51.482 --> 13:54.703
Oh, SeaWorld to Disney
is on fire.

13:54.834 --> 13:57.314
[thinking] Her "successful"
Harvard graduate son

13:57.445 --> 13:58.576
drives a cab?

13:58.707 --> 14:01.362
Do you like the beaded
seat cushion I got you?

14:01.492 --> 14:04.539
Well, I think it's okay,
but my back is loving it.

14:04.669 --> 14:06.802
[rattling]It's like getting a massage
every time I move.

14:06.933 --> 14:07.803
[chuckles]

14:07.934 --> 14:09.544
Something isn't right.

14:09.674 --> 14:11.589
He must own
the entire cab company.

14:11.720 --> 14:12.895
Yeah, that's gotta be it.

14:15.158 --> 14:18.205
Oh, wow, that was fast.
We're here.

14:18.335 --> 14:21.382
Do you think Horace would mind
dropping me off on his way home?

14:21.512 --> 14:23.558
What do you mean?
I amhome.

14:23.688 --> 14:25.603
[car doors open, close] He lives with his parents?

14:25.734 --> 14:27.170
What the hell is going on here?

14:27.301 --> 14:28.215
[knocks]

14:28.345 --> 14:29.564
Do you want to get out?

14:29.694 --> 14:31.435
This is kinda
how dogs die.

14:31.566 --> 14:34.874
So, uh, while we wait
for Louis to pick you up,

14:35.004 --> 14:36.092
you care for a tour?

14:36.223 --> 14:37.746
Of your lie factory?

14:37.877 --> 14:38.921
I'd love to.

14:39.052 --> 14:41.968
It's embarrassing,
but most of our wall space

14:42.098 --> 14:44.535
is dedicated
to Horace.

14:44.666 --> 14:46.973
And here's his diploma.

14:47.103 --> 14:49.366
Okay, at least
the degree is real.

14:49.497 --> 14:50.890
Horace Lee.

14:51.020 --> 14:52.326
Bachelor's Degree in Art.

14:52.456 --> 14:54.110
Isn't it amazing?

14:54.241 --> 14:54.894
Art?

14:55.024 --> 14:57.766
You spent 200 grand
on an art degree?

14:57.897 --> 14:59.420
And it didn't cost us
a dime.

14:59.550 --> 15:00.900
He got
a full scholarship.

15:01.030 --> 15:02.640
Oh, at least it didn't
cost him anything.

15:02.771 --> 15:04.251
He started off
as Pre-Med...

15:04.381 --> 15:06.340
[chuckles]
...but then switched majors.

15:06.470 --> 15:08.908
It cost him everything!

15:09.038 --> 15:11.998
Oh, and this,
in my opinion,

15:12.128 --> 15:14.130
is his finest work.

15:14.261 --> 15:18.352
Bill Gates offered him
quite a lot to buy it.

15:18.482 --> 15:19.788
But Horace
refused to sell.

15:19.919 --> 15:23.139
He doesn't believe in
commercializing his creativity.

15:23.270 --> 15:24.706
Horace is a dud!

15:24.836 --> 15:26.621
Elaine completely misled me.

15:26.751 --> 15:28.840
Jessica,

15:28.971 --> 15:29.929
the way
you're staring at me,

15:30.059 --> 15:32.148
I'm sensing
a lot of judgment.

15:32.279 --> 15:34.194
I haven't said
anything judgmental.

15:34.324 --> 15:36.022
Your face and posture
say it all.

15:36.152 --> 15:37.937
Betrayed by my beautiful face.

15:38.067 --> 15:41.636
You're wondering why you took
parenting advice from me

15:41.766 --> 15:43.507
when you disapprove of my son
so much.

15:43.638 --> 15:44.639
She's in my head.

15:44.769 --> 15:46.249
Uh, what do I do, what do I do, what do I do?

15:46.380 --> 15:49.252
Horace might not be
youridea of a success,

15:49.383 --> 15:50.645
but I'm proud of him,

15:50.775 --> 15:51.951
and you have
no right to judge.

15:52.081 --> 15:53.126
I should leave.

15:53.256 --> 15:54.127
Yes, you should.

15:54.257 --> 15:55.084
How did she hear that?

15:56.694 --> 15:57.957
♪♪

15:58.087 --> 16:00.089
How much time till we move
to the Gibsons' pool?

16:00.220 --> 16:01.047
According to our data,

16:01.177 --> 16:04.137
we have four hours
till the owners come home.

16:04.267 --> 16:05.616
[amplified]
Incorrect!

16:05.747 --> 16:07.183
Your time is up!

16:09.055 --> 16:10.099
EDDIE: How did you --

16:11.709 --> 16:13.233
What are you talking about?
It -- It's our friend's pool.

16:13.363 --> 16:14.974
Cut the crap, Edwyn.

16:15.104 --> 16:16.497
Relax,
it's a victimless crime.

16:16.627 --> 16:17.846
Victimless?

16:17.977 --> 16:20.022
The people's trust in the Census
has been eroded.

16:20.153 --> 16:21.981
I'm sorry, bro,
we're not leaving.

16:22.111 --> 16:26.986
[amplified] Eddie Elvis Huang
sleeps with a stuffed animal.

16:27.116 --> 16:30.119
Emery No-Middle-Name Huang
waxes his chest.

16:30.250 --> 16:31.425
Whoa, whoa,
what are you doing?

16:31.555 --> 16:32.992
If you don't
get out of this pool,

16:33.122 --> 16:35.124
I'm visiting the houses
of everyone you know

16:35.255 --> 16:37.300
and announcing
more embarrassing facts.

16:42.131 --> 16:44.220
[amplified] Justice is served,
Census sty--

16:44.351 --> 16:45.265
[bullhorn squeals]Aah!

16:45.395 --> 16:47.745
Thanks for getting me
out of that house of horrors.

16:47.876 --> 16:50.096
Elaine totally misled me
on her son.

16:50.226 --> 16:52.185
To think I almost thought
she was my equal.

16:52.315 --> 16:53.316
I'm out
on the Lee family, too.

16:53.447 --> 16:54.752
I think Julius is trying

16:54.883 --> 16:56.319
to hijack
my friendship with Marvin.

16:56.450 --> 16:58.017
He comes into my house --
myhouse --

16:58.147 --> 16:59.670
and disrespects me
like that?

16:59.801 --> 17:01.803
Al Pacino?

17:01.933 --> 17:03.674
No, that's not
a Pacino impression.

17:03.805 --> 17:05.241
That's just
me being angry.

17:06.373 --> 17:08.766
Wait,
is that Julius' truck...

17:08.897 --> 17:11.030
at Marvin's?

17:11.160 --> 17:12.292
[laughs]
This is good.

17:12.422 --> 17:13.858
Yeah.
[door slams]

17:13.989 --> 17:16.122
Glad to see you two are
having fun. Guess I was busy.

17:16.252 --> 17:17.036
Hey, Louis,
how's it going?

17:18.254 --> 17:18.298
You liking Marvin's
meat grinder, Julius?

17:19.690 --> 17:20.561
We used to use that
to prep beef for our chili.

17:20.691 --> 17:22.345
Or are you two
yucking it up

17:22.476 --> 17:25.348
about how the Cowboys
need to start Marchand

17:25.479 --> 17:27.568
or Lowenstein
or who the hell cares?

17:27.698 --> 17:29.613
Don't tell me.
Al Pacino.

17:29.744 --> 17:31.224
No, I'm angry!

17:31.354 --> 17:34.183
Julius here is trying
to steal my best friend!

17:34.314 --> 17:35.141
It's so --

17:35.271 --> 17:36.707
It's -- It's not cool!

17:36.838 --> 17:38.013
What?

17:38.144 --> 17:39.058
[scoffs]

17:40.885 --> 17:42.322
I thought that Julius
was going to steal youfrom me.

17:42.452 --> 17:43.497
You did?

17:43.627 --> 17:45.542
I mean, you dropped chili
and -- and Ernest

17:45.673 --> 17:46.587
to go meet him.

17:47.936 --> 17:50.069
You know I can't watch it alone.
I laugh too hard.

17:50.199 --> 17:51.592
And you always
bring me back.

17:51.722 --> 17:55.161
You got nothing to worry about.
I could never replace you.

17:55.291 --> 17:56.075
Plus,
Jessica would kill me

17:56.205 --> 17:58.077
if I lost the discounts
on your dentistry.

17:58.207 --> 18:01.080
[laughs]
Okay.

18:01.210 --> 18:03.604
[both laugh]

18:03.734 --> 18:05.954
Maybe I should just
get my casings and go.

18:06.085 --> 18:07.173
Oh, no.

18:07.303 --> 18:09.871
We were making
a sausage sampler for you.

18:10.001 --> 18:12.091
Maybe turn you into
a "sausage man."

18:12.221 --> 18:13.179
Really?

18:15.311 --> 18:16.182
[sighs]

18:16.312 --> 18:17.748
I am so sorry, guys.

18:17.879 --> 18:19.272
I got carried away.

18:20.360 --> 18:22.362
Well...

18:22.492 --> 18:23.580
Well, okay.

18:23.711 --> 18:25.278
[Marvin laughs]

18:25.408 --> 18:28.194
Hey, why don't we cook up
a few links and watch Ernest?

18:28.324 --> 18:29.238
Together.

18:29.369 --> 18:30.152
HONEY: Hey!

18:30.283 --> 18:31.806
I know you guys
are doing something,

18:31.936 --> 18:33.590
but can you
take it outside?

18:35.026 --> 18:36.463
Really, Margulies?

18:36.593 --> 18:38.465
It took curing
a methadone-addicted baby

18:38.595 --> 18:40.771
for you to realize
what you have with Clooney?

18:40.902 --> 18:42.121
♪♪

18:42.251 --> 18:44.123
[indistinct conversations]

18:44.253 --> 18:46.037
Not a low rise jean
in sight.

18:46.168 --> 18:48.649
I did it.
I changed the world.

18:48.779 --> 18:50.651
Think you spoke too soon.

18:50.781 --> 18:53.044
♪ The ladies will kick it♪

18:53.175 --> 18:54.350
♪ The rhyme that is wicked♪

18:56.091 --> 18:56.439
♪ Those that don't know
how to be pros get evicted♪

18:56.570 --> 18:58.224
DEIDRE:
Aren't you two friends?

18:58.354 --> 18:59.399
Why would she disrespect you
like that?

18:59.529 --> 19:01.227
Oh, I can't wait
to find out.

19:02.315 --> 19:04.447
Jenny McCarthy,
what are you doing here?

19:04.578 --> 19:06.232
I wasn't going to miss
the unveiling.

19:06.362 --> 19:08.103
And I knew
you'd be here,

19:08.234 --> 19:10.671
so I figured
I'd give you plenty to judge,

19:10.801 --> 19:12.455
since that's
what you do best.

19:12.586 --> 19:14.457
♪♪

19:14.588 --> 19:15.502
[snores]

19:15.632 --> 19:18.461
Ugh. This argument
is a snoozer!

19:21.116 --> 19:23.031
Everyone,
thank you for coming

19:23.162 --> 19:25.468
and for your support
to refresh this mural.

19:25.599 --> 19:29.864
Without further ado,
I give you "We Are The World."

19:29.994 --> 19:32.736
[crowd gasps, murmurs]

19:32.867 --> 19:34.042
♪♪

19:34.173 --> 19:36.436
You gave the Chinese kid
a math book?

19:36.566 --> 19:38.177
You think that's all
Chinese kids can do?

19:38.307 --> 19:40.179
I don't really
see the problem.

19:40.309 --> 19:42.181
Being good at math
is good.

19:42.311 --> 19:43.660
This is so frustrating.

19:43.791 --> 19:46.272
Forget it,
you are all not worth it.

19:46.402 --> 19:48.143
No, wait.

19:48.274 --> 19:49.231
This isn't okay.

19:49.362 --> 19:50.841
♪♪

19:50.972 --> 19:54.976
It doesn't matter
if it's a good stereotype.

19:55.106 --> 19:57.065
A stereotype
is a stereotype.

19:57.196 --> 20:01.417
Yes, some Chinese kids
enjoy schoolwork.

20:01.548 --> 20:05.247
But some also want to be
rappers, tennis players...

20:05.378 --> 20:08.207
or great painters.

20:08.337 --> 20:11.993
Their parents are proud of them
for what they are

20:12.123 --> 20:14.213
and just want to see them
represented that way.

20:14.343 --> 20:16.258
Wouldn't you want the same
for your own kids?

20:16.389 --> 20:18.695
[crowd murmuring]

20:18.826 --> 20:20.306
Well, I think
it's unanimous.

20:20.436 --> 20:22.003
We'll change
the mural.

20:22.133 --> 20:24.310
Yes.[cheers and applause]

20:26.181 --> 20:27.748
Thank you
for saying that.

20:27.878 --> 20:29.750
You know,
we might not always get along,

20:29.880 --> 20:31.317
but you were right.

20:31.447 --> 20:33.797
If nothing else,
we have each other's backs.

20:33.928 --> 20:35.016
♪♪

20:35.146 --> 20:38.106
I'm sorry I judged you
and your cabbie-artist son.

20:38.237 --> 20:40.239
And if he's willing,

20:40.369 --> 20:42.893
I think Horace should be the one
to fix the mural.

20:43.024 --> 20:44.025
♪♪

20:44.155 --> 20:45.374
He'd be honored.

20:45.505 --> 20:48.029
I'll ask him when his
harmonica lesson gets out.

20:48.159 --> 20:52.425
[thinking] Yikes. [thinking] I know.

20:52.468 --> 20:53.600
That looks much better.

20:53.730 --> 20:57.343
♪♪

20:57.473 --> 20:59.345
You did a great job,
Horace.

20:59.475 --> 21:00.389
Thanks, Jessica.

21:01.738 --> 21:02.478
By the way, I saw your book
in the dollar bin.

21:02.609 --> 21:04.698
No shame in that.
I bought it and loved it.

21:04.828 --> 21:06.308
You and me, we're not
so different, right?

21:06.439 --> 21:07.701
Just two Chinese artists.

21:07.831 --> 21:09.268
Uh-huh.

21:09.398 --> 21:11.313
Oh, Elaine,
meet my kids.Oh.

21:11.444 --> 21:13.359
[amplified] Sorry, Mommy,
no time for chitchat.

21:13.489 --> 21:16.231
The Census demands I escort
these perps to the pool.

21:16.362 --> 21:17.798
How am I supposed to go back
to the public pool

21:17.928 --> 21:19.365
after tasting private?

21:19.495 --> 21:20.801
Back to swimming
in Band-Aid water.

21:20.931 --> 21:23.325
Quiet, Waxy,
keep on moving!

21:23.456 --> 21:25.327
I can see
why he's your favorite.

21:25.458 --> 21:26.807
[chuckles]

21:29.592 --> 21:32.508
--Captions by VITAC--
